Reports reaching National Daily reveal that Real Madrid erstwhile manager Jose Mourinho will be meeting the Los Blancos current manager Zinedine Zidane in Nyon next week.
Recall that there have series of rumours linking the Portuguese Mourinho back to Real Madrid as Zidane is determined to return the Spanish giants to fortune.
 
However, their scheduled  meeting is in a bid for both of them to honour the slated meeting of some Europe’s top coaches, which is having both of them participating in the Elite Club Coaches Forum which will be held in Nyon on November 11.

The event is an opportunity for them to exchange views on the main problems of the European competitions, as well as discuss and make proposals to UEFA regarding the future of the leagues.
National Daily further learnt that other top coaches invited include Jurgen Klopp (Liverpool), Maurizio Sarri (Juventus), Pep Guardiola (Manchester City), Carlo Ancelotti (Napoli), Thomas Tuchel (Paris Saint-Germain), Erik ten Hag (Ajax), Unai Emery (Arsenal), Ole Gunnar Solskjaer (Manchester United), Sergio Conceicao (Porto), Paulo Fonseca (Roma) and Rudi Garcia (Lyon) will also take part in the event.

Meanwhile, Massimiliano Allegri and Mircea Lucescu are also invited, despite being without a team at the moment.

			
